rievance","label":"CM Helpline - Chief Minister's Public Grievance Redressal Cell","value":"1076","scope":"state","source_url":"https://cmo.kerala.gov.in/help-en.php","source_name":"Chief Minister's Office, Government of Kerala","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Toll-free, 10:15 AM to 5:15 PM. From elsewhere in India dial 04711076; from Gulf countries dial 914711076. Used to check complaint status and escalate unresolved/delayed complaints."},{"kind":"url","topic":"grievance","label":"CM's Public Grievance Redressal System - file and track complaints","value":"https://complaints.cmo.kerala.gov.in/","scope":"state","source_url":"https://cmo.kerala.gov.in/","source_name":"Chief Minister's Office, Government of Kerala","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Official state grievance portal, published on the CMO homepage. Login/registration required; complaints can also be tracked by docket number."},{"kind":"url","topic":"grievance","label":"CMO Kerala grievance portal (home)","value":"https://cmo.kerala.gov.in/","scope":"state","source_url":"https://cmo.kerala.gov.in/","source_name":"Chief Minister's Office, Government of Kerala","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Entry point for grievance submission, complaint status, charge-officer lookup and CMDRF."},{"kind":"url","topic":"police","label":"Kerala Police citizen portal","value":"https://keralapolice.gov.in/","scope":"state","source_url":"https://keralapolice.gov.in/","source_name":"Kerala Police","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Official state police portal: e-FIR, petition status (iAPS), THUNA citizen services, police clearance certificates, vehicle fine payment."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"police","label":"Crime Stopper","value":"1090","scope":"state","source_url":"https://keralapolice.gov.in/page/contacts","source_name":"Kerala Police","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15"},{"kind":"phone","topic":"women","label":"Women Helpline (Kerala Police)","value":"1091","scope":"state","source_url":"https://keralapolice.gov.in/page/contacts","source_name":"Kerala Police","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Published by Kerala Police on its official contacts page as the women helpline for the state."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"women","label":"Pink Patrol - Kerala Police women's safety patrol","value":"1515","scope":"state","source_url":"https://keralapolice.gov.in/page/contacts","source_name":"Kerala Police","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Kerala-specific service, published on the official Kerala Police contacts page."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"road","label":"Highway Alert (Kerala Police)","value":"9846100100","scope":"state","source_url":"https://keralapolice.gov.in/page/contacts","source_name":"Kerala Police","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15"},{"kind":"url","topic":"general","label":"Government of Kerala - official state portal","value":"https://kerala.gov.in/","scope":"state","source_url":"https://kerala.s3waas.gov.in/","source_name":"Kerala District Portal (NIC, MeitY with IT Department, Govt. of Kerala)","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Confirmed as the official state portal by the NIC-run Kerala District Portal, which links it in its header and footer labelled 'Govt. of Kerala'. The site is live but sits behind a JavaScript anti-bot challenge (returns HTTP 503 to automated fetchers), so its contents could not be read directly during this check; it is reachable from ordinary browsers."},{"kind":"url","topic":"general","label":"Kerala district directory - links to all 14 district websites","value":"https://kerala.s3waas.gov.in/","scope":"state","source_url":"https://kerala.s3waas.gov.in/","source_name":"Kerala District Portal (NIC, MeitY with IT Department, Govt. of Kerala)","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Official district listing page. Links each of the 14 districts (Alappuzha, Ernakulam, Idukki, Kannur, Kasargod, Kollam, Kottayam, Kozhikode, Malappuram, Palakkad, Pathanamthitta, Thrissur, Trivandrum, Wayanad) in both English and Malayalam."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"electricity","label":"KSEB electricity customer care (toll-free)","value":"1912","scope":"state","source_url":"https://kseb.in/","source_name":"Kerala State Electricity Board Ltd (KSEB)","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"24x7 centralised customer care for electricity complaints and service requests, published on the KSEB homepage. WhatsApp complaints (no calls/SMS): 9496001912.","operator":"KSEB"},{"kind":"url","topic":"electricity","label":"KSEB - register an electricity complaint / service request","value":"https://wss.kseb.in/selfservices/showAnonymousComplaint.do","scope":"state","source_url":"https://kseb.in/","source_name":"Kerala State Electricity Board Ltd (KSEB)","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Linked directly from the KSEB homepage as 'Register your Complaint'. No login required.","operator":"KSEB"},{"kind":"phone","topic":"emergency","label":"National Emergency Number (ERSS) - Police, Fire & Rescue, Health","value":"112","scope":"national","source_url":"https://www.mha.gov.in/en/commoncontent/emergency-response-support-system-erss","source_name":"Ministry of Home Affairs, Government of India","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"MHA's single pan-India emergency number: 'ONE INDIA ONE EMERGENCY NUMBER 112', a nationwide unified emergency response system. Works in every State/UT. Corroborated by india.gov.in helpline directory, which lists 112 as the Integrated Helpline (ERSS) covering Police, Fire & Rescue and Health services."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"fire","label":"Fire Helpline","value":"101","scope":"national","source_url":"https://www.india.gov.in/directory/helpline","source_name":"National Portal of India (india.gov.in), NIC / MeitY","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Listed under 'Emergency Numbers' on the National Portal of India helpline directory (page last reviewed/updated 14 July 2026)."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"ambulance","label":"National Ambulance Service (NAS)","value":"102","scope":"national","source_url":"https://www.india.gov.in/directory/helpline","source_name":"National Portal of India (india.gov.in), NIC / MeitY","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Listed as 'National Ambulance Service (NAS)' under Emergency Numbers on the National Portal of India helpline directory (page last reviewed/updated 14 July 2026)."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"women","label":"Women Helpline (national, toll-free)","value":"181","scope":"national","source_url":"https://wcd.gov.in/","source_name":"Ministry of Women and Child Development, Government of India","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Published as 'Women Helpline Toll free No. - 181' directly by the owning ministry (WCD) as a tel: link on its homepage. Also listed on india.gov.in as both 'Women Helpline Number' and 'Domestic Violence Helpline'."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"women","label":"National Commission for Women (NCW) 24x7 Helpline","value":"14490","scope":"national","source_url":"https://ncw.gov.in/","source_name":"National Commission for Women (NCW)","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"NCW's own site states: 'Call the 24x7 NCW helpline at 14490 for immediate assistance and support', and lists 'NCW Women Helpline (14490)' under its Complaint Redressal cells. IMPORTANT: the india.gov.in helpline directory still lists 7827170170 as the 'National Commission for Women Helpline' - that number appears nowhere on ncw.gov.in (not even in raw HTML), so it appears stale and was deliberately omitted in favour of the department's own current number."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"child","label":"Child Helpline (national, toll-free)","value":"1098","scope":"national","source_url":"https://wcd.gov.in/","source_name":"Ministry of Women and Child Development, Government of India","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Published as 'Child Helpline Toll free No. - 1098' directly by the owning ministry (WCD) as a tel: link on its homepage. Also listed as 'Child Help Line' on india.gov.in."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"senior","label":"Elderline - National Helpline for Senior Citizens (NHSC)","value":"14567","scope":"national","source_url":"https://scw.dosje.gov.in/elderline","source_name":"Department of Social Justice & Empowerment, Government of India","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Published as 'Elder Helpline: 14567' on the Department of Social Justice & Empowerment's own Elderline site, which the ministry homepage links to as the 'National Helpline for Senior Citizens (NHSC)'. india.gov.in additionally lists a landline 011-20893999 alongside 14567 for the Senior Citizens Helpline."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"grievance","label":"National Consumer Helpline (NCH)","value":"1915","scope":"national","source_url":"https://www.india.gov.in/directory/helpline","source_name":"National Portal of India (india.gov.in), NIC / MeitY","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Listed as 'National Consumer Helpline (NCH)' on the National Portal of India helpline directory (page last reviewed/updated 14 July 2026). Note: the NCH portal consumerhelpline.gov.in could not be reached at time of research (DNS resolves to an NIC address but the host refused connections / returned 504), so only the number is cited here - not the NCH portal URL."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"cyber","label":"Cyber Crime Helpline (online financial fraud reporting)","value":"1930","scope":"national","source_url":"https://cybercrime.gov.in/","source_name":"National Cyber Crime Reporting Portal, MHA / I4C","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Confirmed on the National Cyber Crime Reporting Portal homepage banner (MHA / Indian Cyber Crime Coordination Centre - I4C), which reads: 'To report online financial fraud, call 1930' and 'register your complaint at cybercrime.gov.in'. Independently corroborated by the india.gov.in helpline directory, which lists 1930 as the Cyber Crime Helpline."},{"kind":"url","topic":"cyber","label":"National Cyber Crime Reporting Portal (file a cybercrime complaint)","value":"https://cybercrime.gov.in/","scope":"national","source_url":"https://cybercrime.gov.in/","source_name":"National Cyber Crime Reporting Portal, MHA / I4C","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Verified live. Ministry of Home Affairs portal for reporting cybercrime; supports anonymous reporting, women/children-related crime, financial fraud and other cybercrime, plus complaint tracking. Nationwide."},{"kind":"url","topic":"grievance","label":"CPGRAMS - Centralised Public Grievance Redress and Monitoring System","value":"https://pgportal.gov.in/","scope":"national","source_url":"https://pgportal.gov.in/","source_name":"Ministry of Personnel, Public Grievances & Pensions, Government of India","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Verified live; this is the citizen-facing portal. The site states CPGRAMS is 'an online platform available to the citizens 24x7 to lodge their grievances to the public authorities on any subject related to service delivery... a single portal connected to all the Ministries/Departments of Government of India and States.' Supports tracking by registration ID and an appeal facility. Note: it does not cover RTI matters, subjudice/court matters, or religious matters."},{"kind":"url","topic":"corruption","label":"Central Vigilance Commission - lodge a corruption complaint","value":"https://portal.cvc.gov.in/","scope":"national","source_url":"https://portal.cvc.gov.in/","source_name":"Central Vigilance Commission (CVC), Government of India","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Verified live. CVC's Complaint Management System with a 'Citizen Login', complaint status tracking and a published complaint handling policy. Linked from cvc.gov.in as 'Lodge a complaint'. Covers corruption complaints against central government organisations."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"disaster","label":"Relief Commissioner for Natural Calamities","value":"1070","scope":"national","source_url":"https://www.india.gov.in/directory/helpline","source_name":"National Portal of India (india.gov.in), NIC / MeitY","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Listed on the National Portal of India helpline directory (page last reviewed/updated 14 July 2026)."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"road","label":"Road Accident Helpline","value":"1073","scope":"national","source_url":"https://www.india.gov.in/directory/helpline","source_name":"National Portal of India (india.gov.in), NIC / MeitY","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Listed on the National Portal of India helpline directory (page last reviewed/updated 14 July 2026)."}]}